#transformationtuesday MY JOURNEY: 👇 -278lbs! My journey started exactly 501 days ago as your typical New Years Resolution 1/1/16. I was only 25 at the time, weighed 485lbs, wore a size 28/30 and daily activities such as walking, stairs, or even wearing a seatbelt were difficult. I didn't have money for a trainer, meal plan, or workout routine. Surgery was suggested to me many times by worried family members, but I wanted to try one last time on my own to lose the weight before I considered it. I didn't want to feel like I was on a diet, I wanted to change my lifestyle & relationship with food.  I've always worked hard for everything I have, and I decided it was up to me to change my life. I was the reason I was obese, but I was also the solution. I started counting calories, working out 5x a week for 30 minutes, stopped drinking soda & eating out, joined dietbet & weight loss competitions at work, and about a month in started seeing results. My hope is someone will hear my story and decide not to give up. I want others to know how much they are capable of. Most people think you have to be perfect, have everything planned/prepped and cut out everything to be healthy. You don't, but you do have to start & try. Btw, I still eat carbs everyday. I still drink coffee. I've never worked out longer than 1 1/2 hours, i still have cheat meals, not every meal is a salad, & I have 1400 cals daily & literally feel like i eat all day to reach my cals & make sure im always full. It's all about balance, lifestyle change, & not a 'diet.' Since last year I have completely changed my life with diet/exercise & I have worked hard for 501 days. I am now living the life I've always dreamed of, as a new me. We are all different in our journeys, find what works for you, and take control of your life. There's 229 days left of this year. Who will you be?
